I"¾<p>When you consent to us collecting your data, it is saved on a secure database, owned by the States of Mind team.</p>

<p>The only people who can view your submissions to your handbook are the States of Mind Team. This information is used to help us understand how much you are engaging with the course, to develop it and to reach out if we feel you need further support.</p>

<p>We will only disclose information provided to the handbook if we believe you are at risk of harm. In these rare cases, you will be contacted by Bea Herbert who will discuss this with you, alongside a safeguarding lead at your college. See our Terms of Use and Privacy Policy for more information on how we use data.</p>
